   {:e #blake3 "290ada6d8b5cd1c09350a439583330c53067232128707ddd848a5064f253cc70" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Score the dogfood results from DF2-REV using both CCE-specific metrics and holistic 8-dimension evaluation.\n\nSCORING PROTOCOL:\n\nA. CCE-SPECIFIC METRICS (from raw observation data):\n\n1. CONCEPT ENTROPY (H):\n   From the concept distribution query results:\n   p_i = count_i / sum(all counts)\n   H = -sum(p_i * ln(p_i))\n   Baseline: Session 043 H ~= 0.3 (25/29 skew).\n   Target: H >= 1.5 (well-distributed across 3+ concepts).\n   PASS: max-concept < 60% of total memberships.\n   FAIL: max-concept >= 60%.\n\n2. STEERING ACTIONABILITY:\n   From the frontier recommendation scores (0-2) per observation:\n   Mean = sum(scores) / count(non-absent recommendations).\n   If no recommendations were produced, score = 0.\n   Target: mean >= 1.5.\n   PASS: mean >= 1.0.\n   FAIL: mean < 1.0.\n\n3. MULTI-MEMBERSHIP RATE:\n   NEW METRIC (not in prior sessions): Count observations with 2+ concept assignments.\n   Multi-rate = count(multi) / total observations.\n   Target: >= 0.3 (at least 30% of observations in multiple concepts).\n   This directly tests Session 044's CONCEPT-MULTI implementation.\n\nB. HOLISTIC 8-DIMENSION SCORE (from subagent evaluation):\n   D1-D8 mean, each 1-10 scale.\n   Prior baselines: Session 037 = 3.3, Session 038 = 5.3, Session 043 = 6.7.\n   Target: >= 7.5.\n\nC. COMPOSITE SCORE (0-10):\n   composite = 0.25 * entropy_normalized + 0.25 * actionability_normalized + 0.15 * multi_rate_normalized + 0.35 * holistic_mean\n   where:\n     entropy_normalized = min(H / 2.0, 1.0) * 10\n     actionability_normalized = (mean_score / 2.0) * 10\n     multi_rate_normalized = min(multi_rate / 0.5, 1.0) * 10\n     holistic_mean = D1-D8 mean (already 1-10)\n\nD. DECISION TREE:\n   >= 8/10: Close DOGFOOD-2 (t-655e3cf2), close DOGFOOD-EXTERNAL (t-59f761c3), proceed to DOGFOOD-3 verdict.\n   6-7/10: Identify weakest dimension(s). Create targeted remediation tasks.\n     Low entropy -> innate concept descriptions need domain tuning or threshold adjustment.\n     Low actionability -> frontier scoring needs kind_weight parameters.\n     Low multi-rate -> JOIN_THRESHOLD too high for hash embedder.\n     Low holistic -> specific UX/bug issues (address individually).\n   < 6/10: Fundamental issue. Consider:\n     Hash embedder insufficient -> test with model2vec.\n     Innate concepts wrong for code -> derive from directory structure.\n     Architectural flaw in CCE pipeline.\n\nE. RECORD RESULTS:\n   braid observe '<composite score and breakdown>' in MAIN store (ddis-braid).\n   Create follow-up tasks for any identified remediations.\n\nACCEPTANCE:\n(A) All 4 metrics computed from raw data.\n(B) Composite score computed.\n(C) Correct decision branch executed.\n(D) Score + breakdown recorded as observation in main braid store.\n(E) Follow-up tasks created if composite < 8.\n\nDEPENDS-ON: S045-DF2-REV." :op :assert}
